	<div class="section_print">
		<a href="http://www.newwest.net/"><img src="http://www.newwest.net/images/banners/print_friendly_logo.jpg" border="0" style="margin-bottom:40px"></a>
					<h4>Western Book Roundup</h4>
		
		<h1>On the Bright Side, Recession May Provide More Time for Writing</h1>
		<h2><i></i></h2>
		<div class="text-feature_print">
							<p>By Jenny Shank, 5-27-09</p>
			
			
							<p>What happens to newspaper journalists when newspapers no longer exist?&nbsp; That&#8217;s a question that&#8217;s many people are attempting to answer now in Colorado as the couple of hundred people who lost their jobs when the <a target="_blank" href="http://www.newwest.net/topic/article/hickenlooper_says_rockys_demise_will_send_denver_into_a_funk/C39/L39/" title="Rocky Mountain News folded">Rocky Mountain News folded</a> continue to seek new positions.&nbsp; Some of the newly jobless are taking the opportunity to write the book they never had the time to start before--I&#8217;ve heard that there have been a lot of inquiries about jobs and classes at local writing workshops.&nbsp; 
</p>
<p>
<a target="_blank" href="http://www.linkedin.com/pub/patti-thorn/10/98a/625" title="Patti Thorn">Patti Thorn</a>, the former Books Editor of the Rocky Mountain News, is setting up shop as a manuscript editor for hire.&nbsp; I wrote book reviews for her for eight years, and I can vouch for her editing, which always made my articles better.&nbsp; Anyone who needs a keen reader to respond to a book project should contact <script type="text/javascript">
