		<!-- Begin Comments -->
		
		<b>Comment By hal herring, 5-27-09</b>
		<p>That looks like bad news about The Road. I had some high hopes. Will have to wait and see. <br />
<br />
Of all the McCarthy, the greatest, in my opinion, is Suttree, a life changing book, deep and clear. <br />
<br />
But I think my favorite is the first one, The Orchard Keeper, and my favorite scene in it is when the law comes to get the old ginseng digger, and he shoots them off his porch, slams the front door in a hail of bullets, rolls behind the woodstove for cover, reloads his ancient single shot shotgun,  AND ROLLS A CIGARETTE while waiting for them to try and bust through the door!<br />
<br />
Now that is style.</p>
		
		<b>Comment By Bill Croke, 5-27-09</b>
		<p>Jenny, Of course!!!Writing workshops for journalists. Doesn't that tip anybody off as to why newspapers are dying in the first place? And what would the books be about? What I saw at the meltdown that I had an integral role in causing, etc.? Besides, I thought they all went to work for the government. The one's in Washington and New York do. Well, I suppose if you finally take on the role of a political hack on somebody's payroll you can't be called a hypocrite, just an ex-hypocrite. What do you think, Hal? PS--Nice post on Cormac McCarthy, whom I once had enormous respect for until he got Oprahized. Oh well, who can blame him. He endured unspeakable poverty for years. And now I read that he has a new wife who's busily spending all his money. So it goes.</p>
		
		<b>Comment By KotenokMyrka, 5-27-09</b>
		<p>Чекан друзей тоже надо учитывать. Дональд Трамп, скажем, для двадцатку потянет.</p>
		
